---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "How to Start Investing with $100: A Practical Guide for Beginners",
    "description": "A practical guide to micro-investing. Learn about fractional shares, round-up apps, the $100/month strategy, and how to avoid fees while building your wealth.",
    "datePublished": "2026-03-24",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-24",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Westmount Research"
    },
    "publisher": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Westmount Research",
      "url": "https://westmountfundamentals.com"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I really start investing with just $100?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes! Thanks to fractional shares and zero-commission brokers, $100 is more than enough to start building a diversified portfolio. You no longer need thousands of dollars to buy a single share of expensive companies."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are round-up apps like Acorns worth it?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Round-up apps are great for building the habit of saving without thinking about it. However, be mindful of their monthly fees. A $3/month fee on a $100 account is a massive 36% annual drag. They are best used as stepping stones."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What should I buy with my first $100?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For most beginners, putting that $100 into a broad market index fund (like an S&P 500 ETF or Total Stock Market ETF) is the safest and most effective strategy. It gives you instant diversification."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When should I move from a micro-investing app to a real brokerage?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Once you have built a balance of $500 to $1,000, or when you are ready to set up automated monthly transfers of $50 or more, it's usually time to graduate to a full-service, zero-fee broker like Fidelity, Vanguard, or Schwab."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do I have to pay fees when buying fractional shares?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "At major brokerages like Fidelity or Schwab, there are no commissions to buy fractional shares. However, micro-investing apps often charge a flat monthly subscription fee, which can disproportionately hurt small accounts."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Can I really start investing with just $100?",
    a: "Yes! Thanks to fractional shares and zero-commission brokers, $100 is more than enough to start building a diversified portfolio. You no longer need thousands of dollars to buy a single share of expensive companies."
  },
  {
    q: "Are round-up apps like Acorns worth it?",
    a: "Round-up apps are great for building the habit of saving without thinking about it. However, be mindful of their monthly fees. A $3/month fee on a $100 account is a massive 36% annual drag. They are best used as stepping stones."
  },
  {
    q: "What should I buy with my first $100?",
    a: "For most beginners, putting that $100 into a broad market index fund (like an S&P 500 ETF or Total Stock Market ETF) is the safest and most effective strategy. It gives you instant diversification."
  },
  {
    q: "When should I move from a micro-investing app to a real brokerage?",
    a: "Once you have built a balance of $500 to $1,000, or when you are ready to set up automated monthly transfers of $50 or more, it's usually time to graduate to a full-service, zero-fee broker like Fidelity, Vanguard, or Schwab."
  },
  {
    q: "Do I have to pay fees when buying fractional shares?",
    a: "At major brokerages like Fidelity or Schwab, there are no commissions to buy fractional shares. However, micro-investing apps often charge a flat monthly subscription fee, which can disproportionately hurt small accounts."
  }
];

---

<SiteLayout
  site="westmount"
  title="How to Start Investing with $100 (2026 Guide)"
  description="A practical guide to micro-investing. Learn about fractional shares, round-up apps, the $100/month strategy, and how to avoid fees while building your wealth."
  canonical="https://westmountfundamentals.com/start-investing-100-dollars"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="container">
    <header>
      <span class="badge">Micro-Investing</span>
      <h1>How to Start Investing with $100</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A practical guide to building wealth starting with a single Benjamin.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="guide-section">
      <div class="guide-content">
        <h2>The Fractional Revolution</h2>
        <p>A decade ago, investing required significant capital. If a stock cost $3,000 a share, you needed at least $3,000 to buy in. Brokerages also charged hefty commission fees (often $7 to $10) for every single trade you made.</p>
        <p>Today, the landscape has completely transformed thanks to <strong>fractional shares</strong>. You can now buy a "slice" of a company based on a dollar amount rather than a share amount. If you have $100, you can buy exactly $100 worth of Apple, Amazon, or a broad market index fund, regardless of the current share price.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="data-section">
      <h2>Micro-Investing Apps: Stepping Stones</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Apps like Acorns and Stash popularized micro-investing by linking to your debit card and investing your spare change. Here's how to view them.</p>

      <div class="data-grid">
        <div class="data-card">
          <h3>The "Round-Up" Mechanism</h3>
          <p>You buy a coffee for $3.50. The app rounds the purchase up to $4.00 and invests the $0.50 difference. It's a frictionless way to build the psychological habit of saving without feeling the pain of budgeting.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="data-card">
          <h3>The Fee Trap</h3>
          <p>Micro-investing apps are notorious for flat monthly fees. A $3/month fee doesn't sound like much, but on a $100 account, that's a 36% annual drag on your portfolio. <strong>Fee awareness is critical.</strong></p>
        </div>
        <div class="data-card">
          <h3>The Stepping Stone</h3>
          <p>Use these apps to build your first $500, but don't stay forever. Once you have built the habit, the goal is to graduate to a traditional brokerage where you can automate larger transfers without the monthly subscription fees.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="strategy-section">
      <h2>The $100/Month Strategy: What to Buy</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">If you can commit to investing $100 every single month, you don't need to overcomplicate your portfolio. Keep it incredibly simple.</p>

      <div class="strategy-content">
        <div class="fund-type">
          <div class="fund-header">
            <h3>1. Total Market Index Fund (ETF)</h3>
            <span class="allocation">100% Allocation for Beginners</span>
          </div>
          <p>With a small account, don't try to pick individual stocks. Put your $100 into a single ETF that buys the entire stock market. This provides instant diversification across thousands of companies.</p>
          <div class="fund-examples">
            <span><strong>Vanguard:</strong> VTI</span>
            <span><strong>iShares:</strong> ITOT</span>
            <span><strong>Schwab:</strong> SCHB</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="steps-section">
      <h2>The Roadmap: $100 to $10,000</h2>
      <ol class="numbered-steps">
        <li><strong>Start the Habit:</strong> Use a micro-investing app or open a zero-minimum brokerage account. Automate a $25 weekly transfer (which equals $100/month).</li>
        <li><strong>Buy the Market:</strong> Buy fractional shares of a broad market index fund (like VTI) every time the cash hits your account. Ignore the daily news.</li>
        <li><strong>Watch Out for Fees:</strong> Ensure you are using a broker that charges $0 commission for trades and has zero account maintenance fees (e.g., Fidelity, Vanguard, Schwab).</li>
        <li><strong>Graduate:</strong> Once your balance reaches $1,000, you have graduated. If you are still using a subscription-based app (like Acorns), transfer your assets to a traditional zero-fee broker.</li>
        <li><strong>Increase the Rate:</strong> Whenever you get a raise or pay off a debt, increase your automated transfer. From $100/month to $200, then $500. Consistency is the secret.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-section">
      <div class="guide-content">
        <h2>Common Beginner Mistakes</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Letting Cash Sit Uninvested:</strong> Transferring $100 to a brokerage account does not automatically invest it. You have to execute a "buy" order for an ETF or stock. Otherwise, it just sits in cash.</li>
          <li><strong>Buying "Cheap" Stocks:</strong> A stock trading at $2 is not necessarily a better deal than a stock trading at $2,000. Price per share is irrelevant. Focus on the total value of your fractional investment.</li>
          <li><strong>Trading Too Often:</strong> The fastest way to lose $100 is to try day trading it. Buy a broad index fund and hold it for decades.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        {faqs.map(faq => (
          <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-q">
              {faq.q}
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-a">{faq.a}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 20px;
  }
  a {
    color: var(--accent-color);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* Header */
  header {
    padding: 40px 0 20px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }
  .badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent-color);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  header h1 {
    font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  header p.subtitle {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 18px;
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  /* Guide section */
  .guide-section {
    margin: 32px 0;
  }
  .guide-section h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .guide-content {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 32px;
  }
  .guide-content h3 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 20px;
    margin: 24px 0 12px;
  }
  .guide-content h3:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .guide-content p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    font-size: 16px;
  }
  .guide-content p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .guide-content ul {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .guide-content li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  /* Data Section (3 columns) */
  .data-section {
    margin: 40px 0;
  }
  .data-section h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .section-desc {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .data-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
  }
  .data-card {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 24px;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .data-card h3 {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--accent-color);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .data-card p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-size: 15px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Strategy Section */
  .strategy-section {
    margin: 40px 0;
  }
  .strategy-section h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .strategy-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .fund-type {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 20px;
  }
  .fund-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding-bottom: 8px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .fund-header h3 {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--accent-color);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .allocation {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #22c55e;
    background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1);
    padding: 4px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .fund-type p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .fund-examples {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    padding: 12px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  /* Steps/Lists */
  .steps-section {
    margin: 40px 0;
  }
  .steps-section h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .checklist {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .checklist li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 28px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 16px 16px 16px 40px;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .checklist li::before {
    content: "✓";
    position: absolute;
    left: 16px;
    top: 16px;
    color: #22c55e;
    font-weight: bold;
  }
  .numbered-steps {
    padding-left: 0;
    counter-reset: step-counter;
    list-style: none;
  }
  .numbered-steps li {
    counter-increment: step-counter;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 48px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 16px 16px 16px 56px;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .numbered-steps li::before {
    content: counter(step-counter);
    position: absolute;
    left: 16px;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    background: var(--accent-color);
    color: white;
    width: 28px;
    height: 28px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  /* FAQ Section */
  .faq-section {
    margin: 40px 0 60px;
  }
  .faq-section h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .faq-item {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .faq-q {
    padding: 16px 20px;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    user-select: none;
  }
  .faq-q:hover {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
  }
  .faq-icon {
    font-size: 20px;
    color: var(--accent-color);
    font-weight: normal;
    transition: transform 0.2s;
  }
  .faq-a {
    padding: 0 20px 16px;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    display: none;
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--border-color);
    margin-top: 8px;
    padding-top: 16px;
  }
  .faq-item.open .faq-a {
    display: block;
  }
  .faq-item.open .faq-icon {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Simple client-side script for FAQ accordion
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const questions = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-q');
    questions.forEach(q => {
      q.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const item = q.parentElement;
        item.classList.toggle('open');
      });
    });
  });
</script>
